comments.comment_body:
Didn't Biden propose repealing the cap on the Salt Tax?  
@PaulKrugman - is the salt tax a punitive tax on wealthy households?  

"no tax relief for the rich.... UNLESS that is they are in a democratic state???"

Alright, no bite. Let me put it this way with edits;

If we are ruled for three years by a German Shepherd who has barked day in and day out taking away the smiles and sanity of many, why would we criticize the Cocker Spaniels and poodles of the party for practicing their barking to be a bunch of really good barkers to sound smarter and less irritating than the German Shepherd?

"Life is a Carnival, believe it or not" Let the barkers shout. Please. With corrections, of course!

@George Plant. 
Thanks for this quote, George.  Your words express my attitude, totally!

"Most Americans are sick of the deranged trump train. Please, make it stop, I wanna get off this train."

@Dick

Your dog, like the democrats, need too keep their eyes on the prize, the frisbee, in your dogs case, and the White House, in the democrats case. And in that order. A spectacular frisbee catch would be to take back the Senate. You know, it’s totally possible, after Nixon was impeached the election happened that year. The Democrats won the nationwide popular vote for the House of Representatives by a margin of 16.8 points. This translated to a net gain of 49 seats from the Republicans, increasing the party's majority above the two-thirds mark. The Democrats made a net gain of four Senate seats from the Republicans. 

So if you look at it from a historical point of view, impeachment and trial (even though Nixon resigned before the vote happened) especially when the evidence is overwhelming, could definitely work in the democrats favor. I believe that Trump and company have underestimated the public.
